The '''American Physical Education Association''' ('''APEA'''), previously known as '''American Association for the Advancement of Physical Education''', is an [[United States|American]] association, founded in 1885 to support [[gymnastics]] education.<ref name="Hult 54">{{harvnb|Hult |p=54}}</ref>  The name was changed in 1903, to the American Physical Education Association (APEA). And in 1917, it created one of its most influential groups, the ''Committee on Women's Athletics''.<ref name="Gregg2007"/><ref name="Hult 56">{{harvnb|Hult |p=56}}</ref> The APEA joined forces, becoming part of the [[National Education Association|NEA]]'s Department of School Health and Physical Education in 1937,<ref name="Plowden1996"/> and then forming the ''Division of Recreation'' in 1938.<ref name="Division of Recreation"/>

