{{Infobox organization |name = Bureau of Manpower Employment and Training |image = |image_border = |size = |alt = |caption = |map = |msize = |malt = |mcaption = |abbreviation = |motto = |formation = 1976 |extinction = |type = |status = |purpose = |headquarters = [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]] |location = |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = Bangladesh |members = |language = Bengali |leader_title = |leader_name = |main_organ = |parent_organization = |affiliations = |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = [http://www.bmet.gov.bd/ Bureau of Manpower Employment and Training] |remarks =130635 }}
'''Bureau of Manpower Employment and Training''' is government department that is responsible for the training and employment of Bangladeshi overseas and is located in [[Dhaka]], [[Bangladesh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Manpower export rises|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/backpage/manpower-export-rises-171661|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017|language=en|date=13 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Female overseas jobseekers’ selection starts May 24|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/country/female-overseas-jobseekers%E2%80%99-selection-starts-may-24-83605|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017}}</ref>
==History== Bureau of Manpower Employment and Training was established in 1976 under the Ministry of Manpower Development and Social Welfare as a department.<ref>{{cite web|title=BMET|url=http://www.bmet.gov.bd/BMET/index|website=bmet.gov.bd|accessdate=11 October 2017}}</ref> They provide Bangladeshi workers with Smart cards, Biometric registration, and immigration clearance.<ref>{{cite web|title=Immigration clearance service in Ctg starts today|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/city/immigration-clearance-service-ctg-starts-today-1261984|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017|language=en|date=31 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Private agencies postpone strike|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news/private-agencies-postpone-strike|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017|language=en|date=19 April 2013}}</ref> The Bureau explores the opportunities for Bangladeshi labor force outside the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Matching education, training, skills and jobs|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/supplements/25th-anniversary-special-part-3/matching-education-training-skills-and-jobs-211543|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017|language=en|date=3 February 2016}}</ref> It operates the [[Institute of Marine Technology]] and runs it under its supervision among other technical educational centres.<ref>{{cite web|title=Bangladeshis detained, harassed at Malaysian airport: Adilur|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/city/bangladeshis-detained-harassed-malaysian-airport-adilur-1437352|website=The Daily Star|accessdate=11 October 2017|language=en|date=23 July 2017}}</ref>
