{{Infobox university | name = Delmon University for Science & Technology | native_name = <big>جامعة دلمون للعلوم والتكنولوجيا</big> | image_name = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | motto = | established = 2003 | closed = | type = [[Public university]] | calendar = | chairman = Rifa'at Al Fao'ori | chancellor = | president = Hany Helal | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | rector = | principal = | dean = Ahmad Arbab | director = | city = [[Manama]] | state = | province = | country = [[Bahrain]] | coor = | former_names = | free_label = | free = | colors = | website = [http://delmon.edu.bh/ http://delmon.edu.bh] | logo = }}
'''Delmon University for Science & Technology''' (often shortened to '''Delmon University''') is a private university in [[Manama]], [[Bahrain]].<ref>[http://yp.theemiratesnetwork.com/biz/Bahrain/Manama/Delmon_University_for_Science_and_Technology_102162.html Delmon University for Science and Technology], [http://yp.theemiratesnetwork.com/ TEN Yellow Pages], The Emirates Network.</ref>
The university was originally conceived in 2003 by its founder, Dr Hassan Al-Qadhi.<ref>[http://www.delmonuniversity.com/preview.php?page=historical_background Historical Background] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100923184311/http://www.delmonuniversity.com/preview.php?page=historical_background |date=2010-09-23 }}, Delmon University, Bahrain.</ref> It was licensed to operate on 6 July 2004. The name derives from [[Delmon]] or Dilmun, a land mentioned by [[Ancient Iraq]]i civilizations as a source of raw material, which has been speculated to have been in Bahrain.
Degree programs include a [[Bachelor of Arts]] in [[Business Administration]].<ref>[http://www.qaa.edu.bh/UsersFiles/HERU/HERU%20english/HERU%20-%20Delmon%20BBA%20Program%20-%20En.pdf Program Review Report: Bachelor of Arts in Business Administration — Programme] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706145130/http://www.qaa.edu.bh/UsersFiles/HERU/HERU%20english/HERU%20-%20Delmon%20BBA%20Program%20-%20En.pdf |date=2011-07-06 }}, [[Higher Education Review Unit]], [[Quality Assurance Authority for Education and Training]], Bahrain.</ref>
