'''Gask''', or ''gasque'', is a kind of [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[student]] [[party]] which starts with a more or less formal dinner. The word is believed to have originated from the card game [[vira (game)|vira]], popular in the 19th century.

In some cities, gask is generally used to refer to a party with a formal dress code. Students at [[Stockholm University]] and the [[Royal Institute of Technology]] generally use the term gasque to refer to a gask where the dress code is a [[student boilersuit]].

In some cases, Gasque might also be the name of an actual building, often a building belonging to the [[Students' union|student union]] arranging the gasque, as in the case of [[Chalmers University of Technology]] in [[Gothenburg]].

Many universities also have thematic gasques, as well as slasques, which are less tidy gatherings.


